- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new algorithm for clustering nodes on graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithms. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new algorithm that uses soft modularity loss and attention models for unsupervised community detection, which falls under the umbrella of AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses attention models, which are a type of neural network, for community detection on graphs.
